properties.otherAdvice:
Changed traffic conditions for night works will be in place from 7pm Sunday 30 June to 5am Friday 5 July, weather permitting.

 A temporary speed of 60km/h will remain in place through the project work zone during ongoing day work, and a reduction to 40km/h during night works.

Over Size Over Mass operators with a ground contact wider than 3.2m and/or overall width greater than 4.5m are advised to contact the project team at least one day ahead of movement on 1800 515 141. Significant delays will occur if no contact is made.

  • Contraflow will be in place on the inbound lane from the Newcastle Inner City Bypass to Ironbark Creek bridge from Sunday 30 June to Thursday 4 July.  The right-hand turn lane from Maitland Road into the Newcastle Inner City Bypass will be temporarily closed. Traffic will detour via Wallsend Road.
  •  Lane closures on the inbound and outbound lanes of Maitland Road around Ironbark Creek bridge from Sunday 30 June to Thursday 4 July. 
  • Lane closures on the inbound and outbound lanes of Maitland Road, between Old Maitland Road, Hexham and Hexham Station on Wednesday 3 July from 6.30pm to 5.30am. 
  •  Lane closures on the inbound and outbound lanes of Maitland Road between Sparke Street and Old Maitland Road on Thursday 4 July.
